						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone near the chāvaḍi</hi></p>						

						<p>Mahādēva—A.D. 1268-69.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription is dated in the <hi rend="bold">9th year</hi> of the reign of <hi rend="bold">Mahādēva.</hi> Further details of the date are lost. The 9th year of the reign of Mahādēva would be A.D. <hi rend="bold">1268-69.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records the death of a Jaina <hi rend="italic">(āchārya ?)</hi> of the <hi rend="italic">basadi</hi> of <hi rend="bold">[Hatti]-yamattura</hi> by the rite of <hi rend="italic">samādhi.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
